**How to install the Map:**
===========================

Download the map unpack, go to your steam folder and put it like the following:

\Steam\SteamApps\common\Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps


How to surf offline:
====================

-right click on your steam logo in your taskbar

-choose library

-right click Counter Strike: Source

-click properties

-Generally then specify start options

-type in -tickrate 66 -console


After this the console will open when you start the game,
Now you can type in the surf settings:
================================================================================================


sv_airaccelerate 150

sv_enablebunnyhopping 1

**Surf_Aether**
==================

 the map is a single stage linear surf map set in a floating compound like structure with copious amounts of metal walls with glass in-lays. This o-so-conveniently  allows the light in rather nicely and allows it to reflect heavily off the various smooth glass ramps. Obviously this isn't shooting for realism, more for the aesthetics.

_Contains 11 secrets!_

**There are NO SPIRALS**

There are very few obstacles at all in fact, its meant to be a pretty fast surf map with good aesthetics.** Overall surfing time is about one minute with no fails.** Although that may be a bit short for you pros out there, this was designed for the noobs to enjoy the scenery, the amateurs to enjoy the challenge, and for the pros to master.

  -Quick Disclaimer-
-------------------------
This is my first surf map I've actually decided to release, so don't be too harsh with the criticism, but I am always open to feedback.

So finally the Map is done :)
Special thanks to Fq for making Stage 4 for me,
and of course Chuck Norris for creating the Credit Room :)

Welcome to Surf_Abhorrence!

To be honest I don't even know where to start with this map.  This map started out as something because I was really bored.  I just pulled something out of my ass for something to do, but after showing a few people some pictures, I got enough half-decent feedback to continue on with it.

Start:  Deagle/Full Ammo

This map is basically a freestyle surf map.  There are a lot of places to fight with the enemy and that of the such.  There are also a lot of things to find in this map.  On the main platform and surrounding, there are Mp5's, Ak's, M4's, M3's and Mac10's.  Above spawn, there are Scouts that line the wall.  Figure out a way to get up there?  It's easy, trust me.

The map is a bit large for a freestyle combat surf, so as advice from a friend, I decided to add a bombsite, which is located above the rear end of spawn.  Of course, for safety reasons, another piece of advice from a friend, the bombsite starts disabled.  At the very end of the surf, there is a double platform with a bunker.  On top of this bunker there is a button that NEEDS to be pushed in order to activate the bombsite, so, sorry if you were thinking about planting right away.  Also, there are some spare bombs and defusal kits on the "Top" platform in the middle of the map.

Thanks to all the people who tested this, and for giving very helpful advice and opinions.

FAJ
Butt

If I've forgotten someone, I'm sorry,  I'm just tired.

Oh one last thing:

Can you find the Awp Room?  Hehe.

Surf_aaaa is a map with 4 levels each with their own different tricks you must perform well in order to finish the map.  I did have lighting for it originally, but it was 32 megs with lighting so I decided to take that out.

Level 1 includes blades that, if you hit them, will teleport you back to the starting spawn. After that, you must surf upwards to get to the ramps that if you touch the water below them, you will die.

Level 2 includes a tricky ramp that pushes you upwards like a spring to the next ramp. Then you must start on the last part of level 2 which tests your ability to maintain speed.

Level 3 has a difficult pipe-like ramp that you must surf across. After that you have to use your jumping skills to maneuver to the next part of level 3. The last part of level 3 includes a long ramp that doesn't stop until you reach the pool of water.

Level 4 is the best of all 4 levels. The best way to win this is to shoot out of the tunnel through the left side and keep holding your left key to be able to reach the first ramp. To have enough speed to make the long jumps, you should hold the opposite key that you would normally use to surf with once you get to the small ramps that turn left or right.
